&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Your Mission:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As we evolve our go-to-market strategy to focus on our Ideal Customer Profile (ICP), the Solutions Engineering role has shifted from a passive support function to a central driver of revenue. This role sits at the intersection of Sales, Product, and Customer Success, acting as the bridge between technical capability and business value. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Reporting to the Manager of Solutions Engineering and partnering closely with Account Executives (AEs), you will be responsible for owning the &quot;technical win.&quot; This is a commercially-minded, high-urgency position for someone who wants to actively influence deal outcomes and shape how our product is presented to the market.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a remote role with a preference for candidates based in Toronto, Ontario or Utah. You will be expected to align with North American business hours to support Mid-Market and Enterprise deals across these time zones.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help win deals:&lt;/strong&gt; Improve deal quality, reduce friction, and increase close rates through strong technical and commercial execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Run discovery &amp;amp; shape solutions:&lt;/strong&gt; Uncover real business problems and translate them into tailored solutions and demo narratives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver high-impact demos:&lt;/strong&gt; Run structured, outcome-driven demos that clearly communicate business value (not feature walkthroughs)&lt;/li&gt;
